text: thumb Lauri Asikainen (born 28 May 1989) is a Finnish Nordic combined athlete. He was born in Savonlinna, and made his senior Nordic combined debut in 2009, at the world championships in Liberec. He was previously a ski jumper, winning team bronze in 2007 at the World Junior Championships in Tarvisio. ==References== ==External links== * Lauri Asikainen's web site Category:1989 births Category:Living people Category:People from Savonlinna Category:Finnish male ski jumpers Category:Finnish male Nordic combined skiers
